page.title: 01North of Dunsford, Devon
page.content: The 4x3km area lying between Dunsford and Tedburn St Mary is predominately a farming one. Four narrow tarmaced lanes bisect the block. These are typical of Devon's winding lanes with high hedgerows creating a sunken lane effect. To the eastern side is part of the parish of Holcombe Burnell and there are two brooks or streams, tributaries of the River Teign which flow south. A small part of the area is within the bounds of the Dartmoor National Park. Numerous small woods and coppices abound within the whole area. As is general now with these types of farms mostly on hilly ground in Devon the main agriculture is dairy and sheep production.
